<DOC><DOCNO> AP880826-0064 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-26-88 0615EDT</FILEID><FIRST>d a PM-BRF--GibsonLetters     08-26 0105</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Gibson Letters,0107</SECOND><HEAD>Man Charged In Threatening Letters Sent to Pop Singer DebbieGibson</HEAD><DATELINE>BARBERTON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A man has been accused of sendingthreatening letters to pop singer Debbie Gibson, authorities said.   Richard Pelfrey, 36, of Barberton, appeared in Municipal Courton Thursday on charges of aggravated menacing and extortion forallegedly making threats toward the singer and her family.   A Summit County sheriff's spokesman, Tony DeLuca, said Pelfreysent threatening letters to the singer's publicity agency in NewYork. Ms. Gibson performed in Cuyahaga Falls Thursday night.   Pelfrey was being held in the Barberton jail in lieu of $3,500cash bond.</TEXT></DOC>